{"parse":{"title":"Pyrotherapy","pageid":20169107,"revid":825913964,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg/220px-Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"172\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg/330px-Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg/440px-Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"470\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fever_Therapy_New_Orleans_Marine_Hospital_WPA190402.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Patient being treated with \"fever therapy\" in a Kettering hypertherm cabinet, U.S. Marine Hospital, New Orleans, 1937</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Pyrotherapy</b> (<b>artificial fever</b>, <b>therapeutic fever</b>) is a method of treatment by raising the <a href=\"/wiki/Core_temperature\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Core temperature\">body temperature</a> or sustaining an elevated body temperature (caused by a fever). In general, the body temperature was maintained at 41\u00b0 Celsius(105\u00b0 Fahrenheit) .<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Many diseases were treated by this method in the first half of the 20th century. In general, it was done by exposing the patient to hot baths, warm air, or (electric) blankets. <sup id=\"cite_ref-1936ednote_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1936ednote-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Use\">Use</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pyrotherapy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Use\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>One example is the <a href=\"/wiki/Malariotherapy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Malariotherapy\">malariotherapy</a>, the treatment of <a href=\"/wiki/Syphilis\" title=\"Syphilis\">syphilis</a> by the introduction of <a href=\"/wiki/Malaria\" title=\"Malaria\">malaria</a>, for which <a href=\"/wiki/Julius_Wagner-Jauregg\" title=\"Julius Wagner-Jauregg\">Julius Wagner-Jauregg</a> won the <a href=\"/wiki/Nobel_Prize_for_Medicine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nobel Prize for Medicine\">Nobel Prize for Medicine</a> in 1927.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel1927_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Nobel1927-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/General_paresis_of_the_insane\" title=\"General paresis of the insane\">general paresis of the insane</a> caused by <a href=\"/wiki/Neurosyphilis\" title=\"Neurosyphilis\">neurosyphilis</a> was effectively overcome by the method.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pyrotherapy was also employed in <a href=\"/wiki/Psychiatry\" title=\"Psychiatry\">psychiatry</a>. Of note here is the use of <a href=\"/wiki/Sulfozinum\" title=\"Sulfozinum\">sulfozinum</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pyrogenal&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Pyrogenal (page does not exist)\">pyrogenal</a> that was relatively widespread in <a href=\"/wiki/Soviet_psychiatry\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Soviet psychiatry\">Soviet psychiatry</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pyrotherapy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Natuurwetenschap &amp; Techniek Magazine, october 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-1936ednote-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1936ednote_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Epstein NN (May 1936). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1761228\">\"Artificial Fever as a Therapeutic Procedure\"</a>. <i>Cal West Med</i>. <b>44</b> (5): 357\u20138. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Central\" title=\"PubMed Central\">PMC</a>&#160;<span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1761228\">1761228</a>&#8239;<img alt=\"Freely accessible\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/9px-Lock-green.svg.png\" title=\"Freely accessible\" width=\"9\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/14px-Lock-green.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/18px-Lock-green.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"813\" /></span>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18743642\">18743642</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Cal+West+Med&amp;rft.atitle=Artificial+Fever+as+a+Therapeutic+Procedure&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=357-8&amp;rft.date=1936-05&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1761228&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F18743642&amp;rft.au=Epstein+NN&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1761228&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APyrotherapy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Nobel1927-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Nobel1927_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1927/\">The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1927</a>, \"for his discovery of the therapeutic value of malaria inoculation in the treatment of dementia paralytica\" - NobelPrize.org </span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Charles B. Barton (November 13, 2014). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://mendyourbody.com\">\"Neuromuscular Therapy Procedure\"</a>. <i>Human Repair Services</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Human+Repair+Services&amp;rft.atitle=Neuromuscular+Therapy+Procedure&amp;rft.date=2014-11-13&amp;rft.au=Charles+B.+Barton&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmendyourbody.com&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APyrotherapy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Raju T (2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/cgi/content/full/117/2/e320\">\"Hot brains: manipulating body heat to save the brain\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Pediatrics_(journal)\" title=\"Pediatrics (journal)\">Pediatrics</a></i>. <b>117</b> (2): e320\u20131. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1542/peds.2005-1934\">10.1542/peds.2005-1934</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16452338\">16452338</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Pediatrics&amp;rft.atitle=Hot+brains%3A+manipulating+body+heat+to+save+the+brain&amp;rft.volume=117&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=e320-1&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1542%2Fpeds.2005-1934&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F16452338&amp;rft.au=Raju+T&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpediatrics.aappublications.org%2Fcgi%2Fcontent%2Ffull%2F117%2F2%2Fe320&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APyrotherapy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pyrotherapy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Braslow, Joel T. (1997). <i>Mental ills and bodily cures: Psychiatric treatment in the first half of the twentieth century</i>. Berkeley: University of California Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-520-20547-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-520-20547-2\">0-520-20547-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88